  "texts": [
    "In Section 3, we recall some previous results needed in order to prove the results on the second type of extensions.",
    "Section 4 is devoted to proving that the Mordell-Weil groups modulo torsion of semiabelian varieties over a finite extension of K[σ] are free.",
    "We also deduce that the Mordell-Weil group of any semiabelian variety over such a field is the direct sum of a finite torsion subgroup and a free Z-module of denumerable rank.",
    "Section 5 concerns the Kummer-faithfulness of K(σ) and of K[σ].",
    "Since the Kummer-faithfulness means that the Mordell-Weil group does not contain groups like Q or Q/Z as subgroups, our results are thought of as describing more detailed structures of the Mordell-Weil groups of semiabelian varieties over such fields."
  ],
